## AI Gateway ‚Äî embed & error contract (IPI-492+)

When changing `services/cloudflare-worker/` embeddings, provider error mapping, or `app/src/lib/ai/provider-adapter.ts` embed/error paths:

| Do | Don't |
|----|-------|
| Reject bad/unsupported embed **before** provider fetch (`400` + code) | Silent remap to `embedding` / chat `default` |
| Allowlist (`embedding`, `@cf/baai/bge-base-en-v1.5`) | `model.includes("gemini")` heuristics |
| Explicit BGE id ‚Üí canonical default entry (ignore override alias) | Let `MODEL_REGISTRY_OVERRIDE` swap under that id |
| Sanitize envelope (`code`, `message`, `retryable?`, `requestId`) | Blind passthrough of provider bodies / secrets |
| Typed `AiGatewayError` in adapter | Callers parse `"embedding failed: 400 {...}"` |
| Map 429‚Üírate limit; 408/504/timeout-sans-status‚Üítimeout; 500/502/503‚Üíunavailable retryable | Treat all 5xx as non-retryable `provider_error` |
| Safe-parse `MODEL_REGISTRY_OVERRIDE`; provider resolve inside try | Uncaught `JSON.parse` / `getProvider` ‚Üí unstructured 500 |

**SSOT wording:** gateway supports Workers AI BGE; Gemini embed *routing* is not implemented ‚Äî not ‚ÄúGemini cannot embed.‚Äù

**Minimum tests:** empty/malformed ‚Üí 400 no fetch; unsupported model ‚Üí 400; happy ‚Üí 200 + 768-d; adapter maps envelope ‚Üí typed error. Prefer live `wrangler` curls for Tier B+.

Plan: `tasks/cloudflare/tasks/492-audit.md` ¬∑ **IPI-492 ¬∑ CF-AI-004c**

